                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-190-off1138 t18310217-190-crimeloc1141"></join>. The prisoner is a total stranger to me. On the 20th of January I heard a noise - I came down, and found the prisoner in custody of one of our men, who had stopped him going out of our premises with some paper.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-190-person1846">
                  EDWARD 
                  LYON
               <interp inst="t18310217-190-person1846" type="surname" value="LYON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-190-person1846" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-190-person1846" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Mr. Roworth. I was returning to his premises, and met the prisoner carrying this paper; I followed him about fifty yards, and asked what he had there - he said some paper, and that he was going home; he requested me to take it, but I refused- he came very quietly back with me, and acknowledged that he had taken it from the middle of the warehouse.</p>
               <p>MR. ROWORTH. This is our paper - the prisoner pointed out the place he took it from, and pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was cast away, and travelled up to london for employ, but could not get any.</p>
